Ser '''Loras Tyrell''' is a recurring character in the [[Season 1|first]], [[Season 2|second]], [[Season 3|third]], [[Season 4|fourth]], and [[Season 5|fifth]] seasons. He is played by guest star [[Finn Jones]] and debuts in &quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]].&quot; Ser Loras Tyrell, the heir to [[Highgarden]], is a popular tourney [[Knighthood|knight]] and ranks as one of the most skilled knights in [[Westeros]]. He was the lover of [[Renly Baratheon]] and supported his claim to the Iron Throne as commander of his Kingsguard. After Renly is murdered and believing [[Stannis Baratheon]] to be responsible, Loras has sworn vengeance, and has joined forces with King Tommen and [[Tywin Lannister]] in the [[War of the Five Kings]].

